      "kwargs": {
        "content": "I’ve completed the requested process for tour J09D:\n\n1. Selected all entries from `decision_table` where `TOUR` starts with `J09D` and used that dataset (as `J09D_temp` in the query) to:\n   - Count equipment numbers (`EQUNR`) per house (`HAUS`).\n   - Set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to:\n     - `EVU` if:\n       - `HOUSE_NUM1 = 0`, or\n       - `HOUSE_NUM1 BETWEEN 500 AND 599`, or\n       - `HOUSE_NUM1 BETWEEN 900 AND 999`.\n     - Otherwise `KSA` if the house has fewer than 3 distinct `EQUNR`, else `EVU`.\n\n2. Enriched results by:\n   - Joining with `eablg` via `ANLAGE` = `Installation` to get `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`.\n   - Joining with `net_master` and `sales_master` via `EQUNR`.\n   - Applying the preference rule: when sales data exists, its contact fields are used and the net fields are effectively ignored; when not, net data is used.\n\n3. Exported the final data to CSV:\n   - Filename: `J09D.csv`\n   - Columns:  \n     `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.\n\n4. E‑mailed the CSV to the EVU team:\n   - Address: `meter.readings@evu.com`\n   - Attachment: `J09D.csv`.\n\n5. Dropped the temporary table `J09D_temp` at the end of the process.\n\nIf you’d like, I can also provide the exact SQL used for documentation or reuse.",
